<paragraph blockId="10.[177,1085,1470,1584]" lastBlockId="11.[177,1085,220,303]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="408" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">
C o m m e n t: The original description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bordoni" baseAuthorityYear="1980" box="[648,777,1470,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Ochthephilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="407" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="besucheti">
<emphasis box="[648,777,1470,1492]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">O. besucheti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a male 
<typeStatus box="[996,1085,1470,1492]" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">holotype</typeStatus>
from &quot; 
<collectingRegion box="[243,327,1500,1522]" country="Turkey" name="Samsun" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">Samsun</collectingRegion>
, Bafra&quot; and 
<specimenCount box="[461,575,1500,1522]" pageId="10" pageNumber="407" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[585,682,1501,1522]" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[748,836,1501,1522]" country="Turkey" name="Erzurum" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">Erzurum</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[891,972,1500,1522]" country="Turkey" name="Istanbul" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">Istanbul</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BORDONI A" pageId="10" pageNumber="407" pagination="75 - 82" refId="ref20260" refString="BORDONI A. (1980): Studi sui Paederinae. VI. Nuove specie del mediterraneo orientale. - Atti della Societa italiana di Scienze naturali e del Museo civico di Storia naturale di Milano 121: 75 - 82." type="journal article" year="1980">BORDONI 1980</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[299,388,1531,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="407">holotype</typeStatus>
was examined and its aedeagus figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="HOZMAN P" box="[845,1016,1531,1553]" pageId="10" pageNumber="407" pagination="311 - 322" refId="ref20514" refString="HOZMAN P. (1985): Beitrag zur Kenntnis westpalaarktischer Arten der Gattung Cryptobium MANNHEIM [sic] (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue suisse de Zoologie 92: 311 - 322." type="journal article" year="1985">HOZMAN (1985)</bibRefCitation>
. Since the species can be reliably distinguished from similar congeners only based on the male primary sexual characters, the identity of the 
<specimenCount box="[643,789,220,241]" pageId="11" pageNumber="408" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
, particularly that from 
<collectingRegion country="Turkey" name="Istanbul" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Istanbul</collectingRegion>
, is doubtful. For illustrations of the internal structures of the aedeagus see Fig. 23. Almost all the examined specimens have a uniformly blackish forebody.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[177,1085,320,434]" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">
D i s t r i b u t i o n: The species is currently known from several localities in northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[255,331,351,373]" name="Turkey" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, one locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[494,578,351,373]" name="Georgia" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, and one locality in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[877,920,351,372]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Iran</collectingCountry>
, suggesting that it is a Caspian element (
<figureCitation box="[423,492,381,403]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="5.[177,222,1537,1558]" captionTargetBox="[177,1084,1003,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-64@5.[177,1084,1003,1513]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of Ochthephilum besuchti (BORDONI) (open circles), O. permutatum nov.sp. (filled circles), O. egregium (REITTER) (open squares), and O. hamatum ASSING (filled squares), based on revised records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5276153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5276153/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Map 2</figureCitation>
). The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[726,807,381,403]" name="Georgia" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Georgia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[858,899,382,403]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="408">Iran</collectingCountry>
represent the first records from these countries.
</paragraph>
